spas
Class Bundle

java.lang.Object
  spas.Bundle
All Implemented Interfaces:
IBundle
public class Bundle
extends java.lang.Object
implements IBundle

A bundle of sensory stimulations. So far, a bundle is defined by its visual and its tactile stimulation. Other stimulations are optional. A bundle may correspond to a physical object according to Hume's bundle theory (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bundle_theory)

Author:
Olivier

getExtrapersonalAttractiveness

public int getExtrapersonalAttractiveness(int clock)
Get the attractiveness of object in the extrapersonal space (out of reach by touch). ATTRACTIVENESS_OF_FISH (400) if this bundle's gustatory stimulation is STIMULATION_TASTE_FISH. ATTRACTIVENESS_OF_UNKNOWN (200) if this bundle has been forgotten, ATTRACTIVENESS_OF_BACKGROUND (0) if this bundle is known and not fish.

Specified by:
getExtrapersonalAttractiveness in interface IBundle
Parameters:
clock - Ernest's current clock value.
Returns:
This bundle's attractiveness at the given time.

getPeripersonalAttractiveness

public int getPeripersonalAttractiveness(int clock)
Get the attractiveness of object in the peripersonal space (within the reach of touch). ATTRACTIVENESS_OF_BUMP (-500) if the bundle has a kinematic stimulation of bump. ATTRACTIVENESS_OF_HARD - 10 (-210) if the bundle is hard but not yet bump. ATTRACTIVENESS_OF_FISH + 10 (410) if this bundle's gustatory stimulation is STIMULATION_TASTE_FISH. ATTRACTIVENESS_OF_UNKNOWN (200) if this bundle has been forgotten, ATTRACTIVENESS_OF_BACKGROUND (0) otherwise.

Specified by:
getPeripersonalAttractiveness in interface IBundle
Parameters:
clock - Ernest's current clock value.
Returns:
This bundle's attractiveness at the given time.
